ShareOverviewSummaryConsolidated Edison Company Of New York, Inc. has worked on four hundred and four contracts worth $247 million USD in obligations from the federal government since FY2007. In its latest active fiscal year (2016), the organization received a total of $16.6 million USD in obligations.The principal agencies it has contracted with are the Department of Justice, Social Security Administration, and General Services Administration.

Principal Agencies
Department of JusticeSocial Security AdministrationGeneral Services Administration


Principal Category (NAICS)
Electric Power Distribution (221122)


Principal Product or Service (PSC)
Electric Services (S112)


Designations
